Global investors  bought a  net 5.71
billion rupees ($103 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  on
July 6, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 2.2 percent to 793 billion rupees, according
to the exchangeâ€™s  website . Open interest reached a record 1.6
trillion rupees on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds bought a net 5.72 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on July 6, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
